Package model

Class Commander

java.lang.Object
model.Commander
public class Commander extends Object
This class is used to instantiate a Commander, which is used as a basic user model.
Author:
TheMind

  • Constructor Details

    • Commander

      public Commander​(String login, String commanderName, String realName, Map<String,​Integer> attributes, int points, Map<Mission,​MissionStatus> missions, boolean isAdmin)
      Primary constructor for Commander class.
      Parameters:
      login - Login ID used for logging and referring to the commander.
      commanderName - Commander name as used in game.
      realName - "Real" GDR name, used for roleplay purposes.
      attributes - HashSet of Attribute, which stores the attributes of the commander.
      points - Points the Commander has.
      missions - A map containing, for each mission, its status (relative to the Commander).

    • Commander

      public Commander​(String login, String commanderName, Map<String,​Integer> attributes, int points, Map<Mission,​MissionStatus> missions, boolean isAdmin)
      Secondary constructor for Commander class, without the real name.
      Parameters:
      login - Login ID used for logging and referring to the commander.
      commanderName - Commander name as used in game.
      attributes - HashSet of Attribute, which stores the attributes of the commander.
      points - Points the Commander has.
      isAdmin - Whether this Commander has admin privileges or not.
      missions - A map containing, for each mission, its status (relative to the Commander).

    • setPoints

      public void setPoints​(int points)
      Setter method for the points.
      Parameters:
      points - The points of the Commander, given as int. Cannot be negative.

    • addPoints

      public void addPoints​(int points)
      Utility method for adjusting the points of the Commander.
      Parameters:
      points - Points to be added or subtracted. Cannot result in the Commander having a negative amount of points.

    • isAdmin

      public boolean isAdmin()
      Auxiliary method to check if this Commander has admin privileges.
      Returns:
      True if this Commander has admin privileges, false otherwise.

    • getMissions

      public Map<Mission,​MissionStatus> getMissions()
      Getter method for the Map of the missions the current Commander currently has accepted.
      Returns:
      A Map containing the Mission(s) as keys and their relative MissionStatus as values.

    • acceptMission

      public boolean acceptMission​(Mission mission)
      Method which checks (and eventually accepts) the Mission provided for this Commander.
      Parameters:
      mission - Mission object that has to be accepted.
      Returns:
      True if the mission can be accepted (and accepts the mission), false otherwise.

    • completeMission

      public boolean completeMission​(Mission mission, Map<Requirement,​Object> values)
      Parameters:
      mission - The Mission to be completed.
      values - The current situation which has to be compared to the mission.
      Returns:
      True if the mission can be completed (and becomes so), false otherwise.
